After looking at the reveal, we can all imply that nothing with covid is fully known. With everything there is always something that could happen or a wrong way things could go. So, how do the people know what to do? They don't. There are many unknowns as I previously stated but with what is known we can decide on some pretty major things. One big debate is the precautions being taken. Do we lift them? Do we keep them? There are many pros and cons to both sides of the debate. If we lift them more people die but we get faster herd immunity. If we don't lift them there is less death but longer time till we have immunity. With these very important things factoring in, many people wonder, what is the best way to go about this? As research continues we continue to find more and more things out about this life threatening sickness but people have questions like, Can we survive a very big summer without the precautions and will we have to shut down again? I believe there are benefits to every side but if we are going to take away the precautions we need to be very cautious and still be careful about the people around us and ourselves.

